## 1. Ethics quiz — Sift-specific check

UK Research Ethics applies (University of London). Most quiz items are clear "no" for Sift, but two areas need a deliberate position written into the proposal so the tutor sees we've thought about it:

| Risk area | Sift's position |
|---|---|
| Children / vulnerable adults | **N/A.** App is for adult self-directed investors. Age-gate at signup (18+). |
| Medical patients | **N/A.** Financial domain. |
| Animals | **N/A.** |
| Environmental / dangerous substances | **N/A.** |
| **Copyrighted material** | **Needs care.** SEC filings are public domain (US gov work). Earnings call **transcripts are typically copyrighted** by the publishing service (Motley Fool, Seeking Alpha). Mitigation: use licensed APIs (`earningscalls.dev`, API Ninjas, Quartr) — never scrape paywalled sites. Document data sources + licences in the proposal. |
| **Personal data (UK GDPR)** | **Needs care.** Watchlists, email, subscription state = personal data. Mitigation: Supabase EU region, RLS, no PII in logs, ToS + privacy notice, data-deletion endpoint. Mention briefly in proposal. |
| Financial advice regulation | **Not strictly ethics, but flag it.** Sift is positioned as a research/education tool — never personal advice. Avoids FCA "regulated advice" territory. |

**Action:** before taking the quiz, draft a one-paragraph note on copyright + GDPR positions so we can answer confidently and reference it in the proposal.

