## 2. Project Proposal — content (the 3-minute video)

The lecturer was specific about what must be included. Structure the video around these in order:

### 2.1 Required content (per the brief)

1. **The project idea** — what Sift is, in one or two sentences a non-technical viewer can grasp.
2. **Template reference** — explicitly name **CM3020 AI, Template 4.2 — Financial Advisor Bot**, so markers can cross-refer.
3. **Motivation** — why this matters. The gap: institutional-grade earnings synthesis (Bloomberg, AlphaSense) costs $$$; retail tools (Yahoo, broker apps) show only the date with zero analysis. Self-directed retail investors have no middle option. Sift fills that gap.
4. **Related work — 2 to 4 examples** (lecturer's recommendation; more is hard to fit in 3 minutes). Both academic and commercial. See section 3 below.
5. **Critical evaluation of related work** — what each one does well, what it lacks, the gap it leaves that Sift addresses. The lecturer was emphatic: *features → benefits → problems → gaps → your work*.
6. **Justification of the concept** — Sift's design follows directly from the gaps identified. Tie back to user needs (self-directed retail investors who want to think for themselves).

### 2.2 Marking criteria (same as topic-1 pitch)

- Displays knowledge of the area of study, previous work, and academic literature
- Critically evaluates previous works
- Project concept is justified based on domain and users

The **background research is the centre of gravity** — the lecturer said it's "in essence, key to the project proposal." Spend most prep time here.

### 2.3 Three-minute script structure (target word counts)

3 minutes ≈ 420–480 words at a comfortable speaking pace.

| Section | Time | Words | Content |
|---|---|---|---|
| Hook + the gap | 0:00–0:25 | ~60 | The opening: institutional earnings tools cost $25k/year; retail tools show a date and nothing else. Self-directed investors are stuck in between. |
| The idea (Sift) | 0:25–0:55 | ~70 | One-sentence what Sift is + the four core capabilities (pre-earnings briefing, live 8-K alert, transcript analysis, surprise classifier). Name the template. |
| Related work | 0:55–1:55 | ~140 | 2–4 examples, ~25–35s each, weaving feature + limitation. |
| The gap → why Sift | 1:55–2:20 | ~55 | Synthesise: what the related work as a whole misses, and how Sift's design fills it. |
| Technical approach (briefly) | 2:20–2:45 | ~55 | RN mobile front, Supabase + Modal back, surprise classifier as the AI core, LLM for synthesis. Stress: backed by SEC EDGAR (free), Finnhub, transcript APIs. |
| Outcome + close | 2:45–3:00 | ~40 | What the FYP submission will demonstrate; reiterate the educational/research framing. |

