## 4. Slide deck plan ("powerpoints")

Slides drive the 3-minute video — keep them visual, not text-walls. Target ~6–8 slides.

| # | Title | Visual |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Title** — Sift, plus name, programme, template ref | Simple title card, app mark/logo placeholder |
| 2 | **The gap** | Two-column: institutional ($$$) vs retail (just a date) — Sift in the middle |
| 3 | **What Sift does** | 4-icon row: briefing / alert / transcript / classifier |
| 4 | **Related work — academic** | FinBERT + PEAD with one-line takeaways |
| 5 | **Related work — commercial** | AlphaSense + Earnings Whispers / Yahoo with one-line takeaways |
| 6 | **The gap, summarised** | Single visual showing what each existing option lacks |
| 7 | **Approach** | Architecture sketch (simplified from `SETUP.md`) |
| 8 | **Outcome + close** | What we'll submit, plus the educational-framing line |

Design notes: high contrast, large type, one idea per slide, no bullet lists with more than 3 items, screenshot/diagram where possible. If using brand colours, pick a palette early (Sift identity) so slides + future marketing are consistent.

