## 5. Video production plan

- **Format:** screen recording of slides + voice-over. Webcam picture-in-picture optional but adds presence — recommended for the open and close.
- **Tools:** OBS or QuickTime for capture; CapCut / Final Cut / iMovie for cuts. Audio: any condenser/USB mic; record in a soft-furnished room to kill echo.
- **Script:** write it out in full (≈420–480 words), cut to 3:00 or under. Practice 3–5 times before recording.
- **Pace:** slightly slower than natural speech. Allow a 1-second pause between sections.
- **Captions:** burn in subtitles or upload an SRT — accessibility + helps markers if audio quality dips.
- **Export:** 1080p, mp4, target ≤200 MB so it uploads cleanly to the submission portal.

